The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Two-fold rise in Bata net 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             Two-fold rise in Bata net 
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Calcutta, April 28: Footwear retailer Bata India Ltd has reported a net profit of Rs 12.7 crore for the first quarter ended March 31, a two-fold increase compared with the same period last year.        
	The company had posted a net profit of Rs 5.35 crore in the year-ago period.        
	The turnover during the quarter rose 19.82 per cent to Rs 225.11 crore from Rs 187.87 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal.        
	Bata India is on an aggressive growth path and has implemented initiatives such as investments in large format stores, trendy collections and keeping the shops open seven days a week.         
	These initiatives have resulted in a healthy 21 per cent sales increase in the retail stores, the company said in a statement.        
	The Calcutta-based company plans to open 70 stores every year.         
	In this quarter, Bata opened 19 stores and renovated nine outlets.         
	Bata India Ltds joint venture with Calcutta Metropolitan Group to develop 262 acres at Batanagar into a world- class integrated township is also progressing well .                                                                                                                                     
